<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-01T10:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-01T10:16:00-05:00" n="837" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6232/8</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-01T11:00:00-04:16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>My May 12, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d837fn1">Not printed.</note>
                                The British Minister informs me under instructions from his
                                Government he has granted a safe-conduct to
                                    <persName>Pauli</persName><note n="2" xml:id="d837fn2">He had,
                                    meanwhile, proceeded by train from Rio de Janeiro to Buenos
                                    Aires.</note> to proceed to Germany via the United States on
                                Dutch vessel <hi rend="italic">Frisia</hi> sailing from here June 4.
                                If he asks for safe-conduct to New York, shall I give it?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>